<h3>Pure CSS arrow</h3>

<p>
	One interesting feature in <samp>columns.css</samp> is the arrow that is done with CSS only. No images. Here is the trick:
</p>

<pii:code lang="css">
/* pure CSS arrow */
.error em {
	display:block;
	width:0;
	height:0;
	border:10px solid;
	border-color:#FFFE36 transparent transparent;

	/* positioning */
	position:absolute;
	bottom:-17px;
	left:60px;
}
</pii:code>

